        <label>*11</label>
        <p>OSPAR Commission, North-East Atlantic Environment Strategy: <ext-link ext-link-type="uri" xlink:href="https://www.ospar.org/convention/strategy">https://www.ospar.org/convention/strategy</ext-link></p>
      </fn>
      <fn id="FN9859582">
        <label>*12</label>
        <p>The Ecosystem Accounts compiled are not OSPAR final ecosystem accounts, they are first estimates showing what can be done to move forward at the OSPAR level in ecosystem accounting terms.</p>
      </fn>
      <fn id="FN9859588">
        <label>*13</label>
        <p>Contracting parties include Belgium, Denmark, Finland, France, Germany, Iceland, Ireland, the Netherlands, Norway, Portugal, Spain, Sweden, the United Kingdom, Luxembourg and Switzerland.</p>
      </fn>
      <fn id="FN9859589">
        <label>*14</label>
        <p>As defined by the OSPAR Convention: <ext-link ext-link-type="uri" xlink:href="https://www.ospar.org/site/assets/files/1169/ospar_convention.pdf">https://www.ospar.org/site/assets/files/1169/ospar_convention.pdf</ext-link></p>
      </fn>
      <fn id="FN9859590">
        <label>*15</label>
        <p>As defined by the UN Convention on the Law of the Sea (UNCLOS), Section 2.</p>
      </fn>
      <fn id="FN9859591">
        <label>*16</label>
        <p>OSPAR regions - Region I: Arctic Waters; Region II: Greater North Sea; Region III: Celtic Seas; Region IV: The Bay of Biscay and Iberian Coast; and Region V: Wider Atlantic.</p>
      </fn>
      <fn id="FN9859592">
